<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870116-0154 </DOCNO><HL> Mellon Bank Forms Two Units</HL><DD> 01/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MEL </IN><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mellon Bank Corp. said it created two special asset management subsidiaries to serve corporate and public pension funds, endowments and foundations.    Mellon Bond Associates Corp., with about $18 billion in assets under management, provides bond management products including active, indexed, dedicated, insured and passive core portfolios. Mellon Equity Associates, with about $2.5 billion in assets under management, concentrates on equity investment processes. </TEXT></DOC>